# Force LF line endings for scripts executed inside Linux containers,
# regardless of core.autocrlf on the checking-out machine. Without this,
# core.autocrlf=true (set in this repo) rewrites shell scripts to CRLF on
# Windows checkouts, which breaks their #!/bin/sh shebang inside containers
# ("exec /entrypoint.sh: no such file or directory" — the interpreter path
# becomes "/bin/sh\r", which doesn't exist).
* text=auto
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
